  "prompt": "What is Alma Mater society?",
  "response": "The term \"Alma Mater Society\" can refer to different student organizations at various universities. Generally speaking, an Alma Mater Society is an association or student body organization that represents the interests of students at a particular university. These societies often engage in a wide range of activities, including advocacy, organizing events, providing services, and fostering a sense of community among students.\n\nFor example:\n\n1. **Alma Mater Society of Queen's University**: This is the central undergraduate student government at Queen's University in Kingston, Ontario, Canada. It advocates for student interests, provides services, and organizes activities for students.\n\n2. **Alma Mater Society of the University of British Columbia (AMS)**: This society represents students at the University of British Columbia in Vancouver, Canada. It offers a variety of services, including clubs, events, and support resources for students.\n\n3. **Alma Mater Society at other universities**: Similar organizations may exist at other universities, often with the same name or similar purposes, focusing on improving the student experience and addressing student concerns.\n\nThese societies usually aim to foster a positive educational environment, support student welfare, and enhance the overall university experience.",
